14:24:23 SQL Optimizer enabled (max 1000 layouts)
14:24:24 Compiler unit is timed at 0.000171 msec
14:24:26 Roll forward started
14:24:26 Roll forward complete
14:24:26 Error executing a server init statement : 22023: SR500: Undefined JSO class IRI <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> --  DB.DBA.RDF_QUAD_FT_UPGRADE ()
14:24:26 Checkpoint started
14:24:26 Checkpoint finished, log reused
14:24:26 HTTP/WebDAV server online at 8823
14:24:26 Server online at 1123 (pid 6301)

Apparently this issues causes at least the spatial index to become unusable once the virtuoso server gets restarted. For example: immediately after loading the data, this query gives result - however, after a restart the result set is empty
Prefix ogc: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
Prefix geom: <http://geovocab.org/geometry#>

Select * {
  ?s geom:geometry [ ogc:asWKT ?g ] .
  Filter(bif:st_intersects (?g, bif:st_point (0, 0), 1000)) .
}
Limit 10

Similar issue: http://ehc.ac/p/virtuoso/mailman/message/32359397/
